Explanation:

The solution uses a single pass through the input (n) to count the number of bits set in each number from 0 to n. We initialize an array ans with size n+1 to store the count. Then, we iterate from 1 to n and increment the count for each multiple of 2 encountered. This approach has a time complexity of O(n) and a space complexity of O(n), making it efficient for solving the problem.

